```julia
function count_model_rows(df_cars::DataFrame)
    return groupby(df_cars, :model) |> g -> length(g)
end
```

This function uses the `groupby` function from DataFrames.jl to group the data by the `:model` column and then applies a lambda function (`g -> length(g)`) to count the number of rows in each group. The result is a Series with the model names as its index and the counts as its values.
